text: Jennifer Ann Kiggans (n√©e Moore) (born June 18, 1971) is an American politician and nurse practitioner. She is a Republican. In 2020, she was elected as a member of the Virginia State Senate. She won the 2022 election against incumbent Elaine Luria to become the representative for Virginia's 2nd congressional district. ==References== Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Virginia Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Politicians from Tampa, Florida
